Uses of Package
ys.succinct.xml.dom

  • Packages that use ys.succinct.xml.dom 
    Package Description
    ys.succinct.xml.dom  
  • Classes in ys.succinct.xml.dom used by ys.succinct.xml.dom 
    Class and Description
    AbstractCharacterData
    A succinct node that implements the common CharacterData API.
    AbstractReadonlyNode
    An abstract node that implements Node API that is common to the read-only nodes of the succinct DOM.
    AbstractSuccinctNode
    A succinct representation of Node that is identified by its position(s) in the SuccinctDom.
    ArrayOffsetStore
    A simple OffsetStore that is backed by the character array and stores the content as is.
    DocumentContext
    An object that holds the properties of the XML document like the XML declaration, URI, etc.
    ElementStore
    An ordered store of the information about the following types of the XML nodes: Node.DOCUMENT_NODE Node.ELEMENT_NODE Node.COMMENT_NODE Node.CDATA_SECTION_NODE.
    NameStore
    An ordered store for the family of the XML names.
    OffsetStore
    A store for the character content that can be read by the known offset.
    OrderedStore
    An ordered store of the character content.
    QNameStore
    An ordered store of the information about the qualified names of the XML nodes.
    SuccinctDom
    An object that contains all the succinct data structures to support DOM API.
    ValueStore
    An ordered store for the XML text content (node values).
